<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="187" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,151,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,440,464]" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">Remarks.</emphasis>
The original description of 
<taxonomicName box="[664,1032,440,464]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Coraebus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="187" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hastanus" subSpecies="ephippiatus">
<emphasis box="[664,1032,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">Coraebus hastanus ephippiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consisted only of the illustration showing the shape of the apex of elytra without any description and detailed label information. We only know that the 
<typeStatus box="[193,241,512,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">type</typeStatus>
originated from 
<collectingCountry box="[435,506,511,535]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">China</collectingCountry>
. According to the general distributions of the species, it is presumed that the 
<typeStatus box="[1387,1435,512,536]" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">type</typeStatus>
specimen came from South-East of 
<collectingCountry box="[551,618,548,572]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[633,702,548,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1272,1295]" captionTargetBox="[270,1314,345,1226]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[257,1330,337,1239]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 7. Distribution map of three subspecies. C. hastanus hastanus;, C. hastanus oberthueri; C. hastanus ephippiatus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215925/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="187">
Fig. 
<number box="[686,702,548,572]" pageId="9" pageNumber="187" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
